ENTRY            M1031   20260123   20260302   20260302       M144
SUBENT        M1031001   20260123   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                 15         40
TITLE      Studying the population of 178m,177Ta in (gamma,xn)
            reactions.
AUTHOR     (V.A.Zheltonozhsky,M.V.Zheltonozhskaya,A.V.Savrasov,
           A.P.Chernyaev,S.V.Varzar,V.V.Kobets)
REFERENCE  (J,PPN/L,18,315,2021)
            English translation of FCY/L,18,249,2021.
           (J,FCY/L,18,249,2021)
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD,4RUSMOS,4ZZZDUB)
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
REL-REF    (R,,V.A.Zheltonozhsky+,J,EPJ/A,57,121,2021)
            Description of the facilities used.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Induced beta-delayed gamma-activity measured.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Gamma spectrometers based on the Canberra and
            Ortec HPGe-detectors (100-200 cm3) with energy
            resolution of 1.2 keV at the 343 keV line of 175Hf
            and 1.8-2.0 keV at 1173 and 1332 keV lines of 60Co.
MONITOR    ((73-TA-181(G,N)73-TA-180,,SIG)+
           (73-TA-181(G,N+P)72-HF-179,,SIG))
MONIT-REF  (M0850003,V.V.Varlamov+,J,PAN,76,1403,2013)
ANALYSIS   Gamma-quanta energy spectrum lines data.
           For adaptation of the experimental spectra the
            Winspectrum program was used.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical errors.
COMMENT    For the first time the flux-weighted average yields
            of 180Hf-m in (gamma,p) reaction were measured by
            activation and off-line gamma-ray spectrometric
            technique at the bremsstrahlung end-point energies
            of 20, 40 and 55 MeV.
           Using weighted-average fluxes of bremsstrahlung
            gamma-rays the weighted-average reaction cross
            sections could be obtained and therefore only
            integrated cross sections are in fact measured in
            experiments.
STATUS     (TABLE,,V.A.Zheltonozhsky+,J,PPN/L,18,315,2021)
            Data from Table 1.
HISTORY    (20211007C) Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
            CDFE by V.Varlamov.
           (20220817A) Corrected by VV and SD: REACTION,
            DECAY-DATA, STATUS.
           (20260123U) Corrected by VV and SD: STATUS.
ENDBIB              40
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           43
SUBENT        M1031002   20260123   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                  5         19
REACTION  1(73-TA-181(G,3N)73-TA-178-M,,SIG,,BRA)
          2(73-TA-181(G,3N)73-TA-178-M,,SIG,,BRA)
            The flux-weighted average reaction cross section.
DECAY-DATA (73-TA-178-M,,DG,426.4)
            Data from Fig. 1.
SAMPLE     The all target were made from the metallic foils of Ta
            of natural isotopic composition.
          1At Eg-max = 40 MeV the target was in form of rectangle
            (0.6 x 2.0 x 0.011 cm), weight 0.22 g.
          2At Eg-max = 55 the target was the in form of square
            (2 x 2 x 0.02 cm), weight 1.3 g.
FACILITY  1(LINAC,4ZZZDUB) 200 MeV electron linac (LUE-200) at
            JINR (Dubna)
          2(MICRT,4RUSMOS) 55 MeV RTM-55 racetrack microtron of
            Skobeltsyn Institute of Nuclear Physics, Lomonosov
            Moscow State University.
HISTORY    (20220817A) Corrected by VV and SD: DECAY-DATA
            corrected.
           (20260123U) Corrected by VV and SD: STATUS.
ENDBIB              19
